# Copy to `.env` for local tooling only. CI uses GitHub repository secrets with the same names.
# Never commit real values.

# --- Chrome Web Store (OAuth client + refresh token) ---
# Official docs:
# https://developer.chrome.com/docs/webstore/using_webstore_api
# As of March 10, 2026, the refresh token comes from your Google OAuth setup
# and Chrome Web Store API scope. It does not depend on store approval.
CHROME_EXTENSION_ID=
CHROME_CLIENT_ID=
CHROME_CLIENT_SECRET=
CHROME_REFRESH_TOKEN=
# Local publish script only; CI sets this from the Makefile VERSION:
# CHROME_ZIP_PATH=/absolute/path/to/FontSource/artifacts/fontsource-chrome-1.0.0.zip

# --- Firefox / AMO (JWT credentials; used by mozilla/web-ext as WEB_EXT_*) ---
# From https://addons.mozilla.org/developers/addon/api/key/
# AMO shows "JWT Issuer" + "JWT Secret"; web-ext expects these names:
#   WEB_EXT_API_KEY     = JWT Issuer   (the user id string)
#   WEB_EXT_API_SECRET  = JWT Secret   (the secret string)
# GitHub Actions: add repository secrets with the same variable names.
# Your add-on must declare a stable gecko id for listed updates (see manifest.firefox.json).
WEB_EXT_API_KEY=
WEB_EXT_API_SECRET=

# --- Safari / Mac App Store (fully automated macOS archive + upload path) ---
# Official docs:
# https://developer.apple.com/help/app-store-connect/manage-builds/upload-builds/
# https://docs.github.com/en/actions/how-tos/deploy/deploy-to-third-party-platforms/sign-xcode-applications
#
# The repo now tracks the Xcode wrapper under safari/ and CI can archive/export/upload
# a signed macOS build for the Safari extension host app.
#
# Export both the Apple Distribution certificate and installer certificate together
# into one .p12 if possible, then base64-encode it for this secret. Apple’s
# import-codesign-certs action supports multiple certs in one p12.
APPLE_CERTIFICATES_P12_BASE64=
APPLE_CERTIFICATES_P12_PASSWORD=
#
# Provisioning profiles for the host app and the embedded Safari extension target.
# Base64-encode each downloaded profile separately.
APPLE_PROVISION_PROFILE_APP_BASE64=
APPLE_PROVISION_PROFILE_EXTENSION_BASE64=
#
# Team/signing identifiers.
APPLE_TEAM_ID=
APPLE_BUNDLE_ID=com.raminfiroozye.FontSourceSafari
APPLE_EXTENSION_BUNDLE_ID=com.raminfiroozye.FontSourceSafari.Extension
#
# Upload authentication for altool. App-specific password comes from appleid.apple.com.
APPLE_ID=
APPLE_APP_SPECIFIC_PASSWORD=
#
# Optional: if your Apple account is associated with multiple providers, altool may
# need this provider public id.
APPLE_PROVIDER_PUBLIC_ID=
#
# Optional alternate path: App Store Connect API key material. Not required by the
# current workflow, but useful if you later switch to Transporter/API-key auth.
ASC_ISSUER_ID=
ASC_KEY_ID=
ASC_KEY_P8=
